receive as a public input a previous scope commitment and as private inputs a delegator scope, a delegator credential commitment, a delegatee scope, a delegatee credential commitment, and a delegatee Merkle proof comprising sibling hashes and a proof index;
constrain that the two-input Poseidon hash of the delegator scope and delegator credential commitment equals the previous scope commitment, providing identity-bound chain linking;
prove Merkle membership of the delegatee credential commitment in the second Merkle tree by computing a Merkle root from the delegatee credential commitment and the delegatee Merkle proof, and outputting said computed Merkle root as a public signal for on-chain verification against a root history buffer of the second Merkle tree;
constrain bit-by-bit that the delegatee scope is a subset of the delegator scope;
enforce a cumulative bit encoding invariant on the delegatee scope;
verify an EdDSA signature of the delegator over a delegation token; and
output a new identity-bound scope commitment as a two-input Poseidon hash of the delegatee scope and delegatee credential commitment.

